Gaius (1, 130) says, ‘exeunt liberi virilis sexus de patris potestate, si flamines Diales inaugurentur, et feminini sexus, si virgines Vestales capiantur.’ This was without ‘capitis diminutio,' such as would have been in- volved in adoption into another family. The ceremony of ‘taking’ was a kind of ‘mancipatio‚’ by which the person came under the ‘ potestas' of the deity, repre- sented by the chief pontifs: see Mar- quardt‚ Staatsv. iii. p. 301.
